After downloading the code from github, set up the local environment.

    $ bundle config set deployment true

and/or

    $ bundle config set path 'vendor/bundle'

If deployment is true, and no path is set, it will use 'vendor/bundle',
so here it is superfluous. If you prefer a different path, then use this
command to set it.

Now simply run:

$ bundle

this will install all gems in the folder osaawebsite/vendor/bundle. 

------------------------------------------

To serve:

$ bundle exec jekyll serve --livereload



------------------------------------------
